	Leaving Las Vegas. Better options down town.	If my wife leaves me, I found the hotel that I will stay at to renact the movie &quot;Leaving Las Vegas&quot;. This used to be one of my favorite places downtown, but in the 4 years since I have been here last it has gone downhill. It seems like the owners are contemplating selliing the land or tearing it down, because they have stripped alot of the unique features of the place away. I noticed the same thing at it's sister property, The Plaza. The rooms were dirt cheap, but they are all cheap downtown. I have stayed at all of the downtown properties(freemont street) over the years, this was the worst. The rooms are dated and dirty. The back area of this casino as been converted into a makeshift R&amp;B Club. No sports book anymore or semi-famous restaraunt on the second floor. They have an asian themed restaurant and a coffee bar, that's it. There are better choices on fremont street. As for Fremont street itself, the free entertainment offered during this stay was the best that I have seen down here.	
Nov 13 2009 	The price is right if you're on a budget	We only stayed here one night because everything was higher on Saturday, and this was the cheapest room for that night ($69 for North tower deluxe).We were the only ones checking in at 1 am, they gave us a $20 free slot play for joining the player's club, but after waiting 40 minutes in line with only 5 people ahead of us, we decided not to join the club. From the lobby, we had to walk through a bar PACKED with people because there was a concert going on. There is no other way through so we had to go through these hundreds of people to get to the elevator.The room was actually very large and of course as everyone said, it was dirty, even for the north tower rooms. but, I expected it after reading the reviews and we weren't planning to stay there for more than a few hours at most. I feel we got a good deal for the money, but I wouldn't stay in that hotel unless I absolutely had no other choice. In this case, the hotel we had booked at charged $169 for that Saturday and I could have booked a standard room at the Vegas Club for $49 for the same day but upgraded to the deluxe.	
