Aug 20 2009 	Downtown kicks the strip's ***!	First off let me say if you are going to Las Vegas to spend all of your time in the room then don't stay in the old hotels downtown. That being said, if you are going to Vegas to experience Las Vegas and the surrounding attractions then you can shower and sleep at the Las Vegas Club and have a hell of a time. No the room is not 5 star but you can get clean and the beds were comfortable. The staff was very nice and we got a ton of comps. Also, there is nothing cooler than the Freemont Street Experience. You had better like it because you will hear it in your room until 2 in the morning. We stayed for an entire week and could not have been happier with the price. We paid less than $200 for the week and we were able to get right out and bounce from casino to casino nabbing cheap drinks and cheap food along the way. There are incredibly cheap shops with all kinds of goodies along the way. It was easy to get around after we figured out I-15 and how to avoid the strip. This hotel is not for honeymooners or rich fat cats but for a guy that was trying to take his daughter on a vacation and get the most for his money is was perfect. We will definitely be going back. Also, we had a first class meal at the restaurant located at the hotel, Tinoco's, and it was incredible. I had the best Chilean Sea Bass that I have ever had. This restaurant will measure up to any place you can eat in Vegas as far as strictly the cuisine.	
