Jul 23 2009 	Service with a smile. The rooms in the two towers are totally different.	The rooms in the two towers are totally different. The north tower opened in 1996 and has huge rooms. If you get a suite on 15 - they are larger than many apartments and have floor to ceiling windows. Most have hot tubs right in the bedroom. Great place to stay for New Year's Eve if you get the side facing the Strip.The south tower has been around forever. The rooms are decent but not as large as the north - and much more out of date in style. They are a fine option for the price though, and the location is great if you like the circus atmosphere of downtown at night when the overhead light show is going and live bands play on weekends.We are &quot;regulars&quot; as you can tell - I stayed here in June, chose to stay here for my birthday in July - and will go back again in Aug. because it just feels like home. The staff is so friendly, the casino odds are way better than on the Strip - and though I miss the Great Moments Room, Tinoco's serves good food with good service. You can use the large pool across the street at their sister property, The Plaza.This place is well worth a try if you don't need the luxury of the Strip and just want to have a good time. They have just booked a fantastic R &amp; B group for weekends and the place is packed so come on down to downtown old style Vegas!	
