Apr 24 2009 	UWMutt	I used to be a regular at the Vegas Club beginning in the early 1990's. At one time, they had a great sportsbook where I would bet and watch football. Sadly, the sportsbook operation is no longer there. The hotel has been going downhill ever since. My current gripes: 1) Parking - They used to have a parking attendant who limited the use of the covered parking to hotel guests only during the holidays and busy weekends. They don't do this anymore. So now, any non-hotel guest can park in the covered parking garage and you might find yourself driving around and around looking for a parking space. One time, I had to park at the Main Street outdoor parking lot and had to walk to the Vegas Club. 2) Ice Machines - They only have two or three ice machines located on a few floors. I don't know why that is so. Maybe it is to cut maintenance costs. So, if you stay at this hotel during a hot summer month, you will be going on a hunting expedition looking for an ice machine...just to discover that all of the ice have already been taken. Overall, the Vegas Club is a good value for the budget minded visitor because the hotel is located on Fremont Street. However, there are better places to stay. I, for one, will no longer stay there.	
