May 8 2008 	Great place to stay on a budget	We stayed the last weekend in April 2008 and, being the finicky person I am about cleanliness, the Vegas Club outdid themselves in this area.It is an older property on the famous Fremont Street Experience, but our room was very clean and we had a great view of downtown Las Vegas. There was ample parking available, the room was spacious, the bed was comfortable and the seating area was a nice touch. It has individually controlled heat/air (unlike most places that have one big, huge window unit) and sufficient closet space for any traveler.The casino is small compared to some of the other big name properties (Binion's, Golden Nugget, etc.) but that's what makes it nice. It's not too crowded at any time and there's plenty of room to get around without being crowded in.Dining consists of a small restaurant, which had really good food at affordable prices, a small sports bar, an ice cream stand and the main casino bar.You're not too far from various dining and shopping venues and you're right at the start of the Freemont Street Experience.Overall, for the price paid, this is a nice place. I would definitely stay here again.	
