Nov 7 2007 	Can't Beat the Location!	Stayed here November 4th for two nights. Although staying at The Vegas Club is certainly not a luxury experience, it's a decent bargain, especially considering price I paid of only $31.50 a night. Plus, you just can't beat the hotel's location, right on Fremont Street. It's also conveniently located right off the freeway. I did use the convenient Deuce Bus Line to visit the strip one night. The bus stops near the hotel and is very easy to use. It's a little slow and a lot crowded, but I was using it at peak time.Parking at the hotel is free and the parking garage elevator takes you right to the front desk. Check in was easy and the front desk agent was friendly enough. I arrived about one hour before their stated check-in time and she let me check-in early without any hassle.The room did smell like smoke...years and years of smoke...but it was a smoking room (room 711 in the South Tower) so what could I expect. It was just worse than I thought it would be. After opening the window and running the air for a little while, the smell got better.The bathtub drain was slow and did back up so I took pretty quick showers. The water pressure was excellent and the window in the shower is nice. For about ten minutes one day, the drain in the tub started making these really loud gurgling sounds. I kept expecting something to start shooting out, but it never did and the noise never returned. Part of the ceiling in the bathroom was drooping from what I suspect was water damage, but for $31.50 a night I expect there are going to be some maintenance issues. The t.v. remote didn't work, but I wasn't in Vegas to watch t.v. so it really didn't bother me so much. I just changed the t.v. manually when I needed to. The air conditioner worked well and being able to open the window was great. The bed and pillows were pretty good, definitely more comfortable than I expected after reading previous reviews. The room was overall in fair shape and the housekeeper who cleaned my room both days was friendly to me and did a good job cleaning the room. I stopped her in the hall and asked her if she could clean my room next because I really wanted to take a nap. She was very nice and cleaned the room right away. The room smelled much better after she had been in there. She must have sprayed it with something.If you're going to Las Vegas to see volcanoes and be pampered then this probably isn't the place for you because it's definitely aging. This hotel is for people who primarily want to gamble and need a safe place to sleep in a very convenient location.	
Nov 7 2007 	Great Hotel	After reading reviews decided to go ahead and book this hotel for 5 nights for myself, husband and teenage son. Cost was £38.00 a night for this 2 star hotel downtown on Freemont street. What a bargain! We had a deluxe room in the north tower which was very spacious and clean but a bit run down. Vegas Club is a no nonsense hotel. The check-in was quick and friendly. We used the receptions safety deposit box - this was well controlled and receptionists looked after us well. There was always hot water for showering or bathing. Room serviced daily. Fresh cleaning smelling towels replaced on a daily basis. Coffee making facilities with fridge in bedroom. Beds were quite comfortable with clean linen. We were in room 520 and had very little noise, but there was a smokey odour in room. Found the hotel to be in a safe area and well patrolled with security. More user friendly than the strip. Vegas Club affiliated to the Plaza hotel where you can use the pool and gym facilities and eat a $7.77 all day buffet. The live show at the Plaza 'Viva Las Vegas' is fablous and excellent value for money. The barman Harry at the Sportsbar in Vegas Club is wonderful. Worked the room and kept drinks flowing even when bar was packed. It was a pleasure to watch him work, very efficient and nothing too much trouble. We would definitely go back to this hotel again - what a place with wonderful staff!	
