Oct 9 2006 	5th Stay At The Vegas Club	With a little play, after your first stay, if you sign up for and gamble with your Vegas Players' Club Card, the Vegas Club will be sending you mailers for comp and discounted room rates. We only stay in The North Tower. Toke the desk clerk $10 to &quot;Pick you out a nice one!&quot;. We get a king N/S. Call housekeeping as soon as you arrive and get more pillows, if you need them. Don't wait 'till you want to go to sleep. Tip a few bucks to the nice person who brings them. Our rooms are always very, very clean, but also very, very, very bare. No clock/radio/alarm. Bring one! No hair dryer. Bring one! No coffee maker. Bring one!!! The bathtub and commode share a room, the single basin sink shares an alcove with the open reach-in wardrobe. There is a make-up vanity with mirror, lights and outlet next to the bed. Bar soap, shampoo, and lotion included. The carpet is beige. Very brave, imo. The artwork is a framed Mediterranean Seaside print. The drapes are not blackout. Each floor has an ice machine and a $1.50 Pepsi/Bottled Water machine. The Upper Deck Restaurant has good diner food, and good, cheap, graveyard breakfasts on sale. The Great Moments Room is great, as advertised, and closed Tues and Wed. Public Internet access across from the gift shop and snack bar. Check-in/ Parking on Ogden. They have liberal rules Blackjack, 5x Odds on Craps, Roulette, Let it Ride, and Texas Hold 'em table games. Lots of slots and VP. No Keno or Sports Book. The staff is friendly! Good luck!!!	
