Oct 5 2004	Great Value!	My friends and I booked a room at the Las Vegas Club through hotels. We got our two queen bed, smoking room for $119.00 a night. We stayed both Friday and Saturday night. This is a good hotel for the down town area, if you want the glitz and glamour of the strip..... stay there, but if where you stay is not as important as what you do, this is the hotel for you.We didn’t arrive until around 3:00 in the morning on Saturday, our check in was very fast, and Cyndi (who is VERY nice, and has beautiful eyes) upgraded us to the North tower, and even put us on the 14th floor. Our room was spacious with a nice view of the Freemont Experience, it also had a not so nice view of the roof tops of the other part of the casino and hotel, but the skyline and people watching made up for that.The only complaints I have about the room is that despite our do not disturb sign the housekeeping went so far as to open our door to come in and clean both days. Our tub would not drain properly, which was pretty gross. Besides that the service was EXCELLENT! I called down to see if we had a concierge service (which they don’t) but the front desk put me in touch with Freddie the bell boy who was very helpful, I was looking for a particular type of restaurant and he went as far as bringing up a flyer to our room, and didn’t even want to accept the tip I had for him. Our check out was very fast and friendly. I told the front desk we did not use the safe, and were not charged for it. As I was checking out, a patron brought up a wallet and cell phone that he had found, and the girl at the front desk went so far as to check and see if they were a guest at the hotel before turning it over to lost and found.All in all it was a great stay, and for the value, and the location I would definitely stay at the Las Vegas club again.	
