Nov 30 2003	Great Room 	Spent 7 days at the Las Vegas Club and found it to be a great experience! I usually stay at the Golden Nugget when my employer is paying, but this trip I was paying my own way and decided to save some money. Check in was very fast and efficient and counter person was very friendly! I was in the North Tower room number 1125. Room was huge, quiet and comfortable! Room had 1 King bed, Sofa with 2 chairs and coffee table, and a great desk for my laptop computer. Room was clean odor free. Only minor complaint was that the bathroom was quite small. Very easy walk from the room to casino and parking garage. I will defiantly be staying there again.	
Nov 6 2003	Great place to stay in Vegas!!!	I booked a last minute trip to Las Vegas to celebrate my friend's birthday. Well, I initially told him I couldn't make it because I couldn't afford the weekend rates hotels charge on the strip. But then, after a little bit of internet research, I found the Las Vegas Club Hotel, located right on the Fremont Experience!! $27 for a Saturday night, $19/night for Sunday and Monday! I couldn't believe it! One thing I liked about the place was that it was easy to find my way out, not like the maze that the larger hotels tend to have to intentionally keep people from leaving.	
Oct 17 2003	Not Unhappy	Fantastic location if you want to spend a day or two enjoying the downtwn area. We had big problems with keys that didn't work. Other guest were having the same issue. But they claimed it was only a temporary problem and it was fixed by the second day. The lobby and casino area were a little to dirty for my taste. The sports book didn't have enough comfortable chairs. At many of the BJ tables you could not double after splitting. The dealers were extremely friendly and the drinks were quick and refreshing. Good specials and quality at the sports themed restaurant on the second floor. We stayed in the North Tower and the rooms were clean and quite nice. Plus they were very handy to the casino. We were comped rooms, food and drinks but we played alot of video poker and blackjack ($20 to $30/hand). Not crowded-quick elevators-effecient valet-cheap--what's not to like. But we all think the Plaza is still our favorite.	
